GangKui Cup
RULEBOOK
I. Schedule & Format
1. Tournament Format
•Tournament Rules: This championship does not offer direct invitations based on VRS List; all participants will be invited on a "first-come, first-served" basis through open registration.
•The tournament consists of 3 stages: Play-In, Group stage and the Playoffs.
•The top 4 registered teams by VRS will be directly seeded into the Main Event (Playoffs).
•Play-In: This stage will be held online. The game server will be hosted in China. The 20 teams will be divided into four groups (A, B, C, and D) and compete in a four round-robin format groups. There will be 5 teams in each group. All matches will be BO1. The top two teams from each group will advance to Group Stage.
•Group Stage: This stage will be held online. A total of eight teams will be divided into two groups of four teams each, competing in a double-elimination format. The Opening and Winners’ matches are BO1, while the Elimination and Decider matches are BO3. The top two teams from each group will advance to the Playoffs.
• Playoffs: This stage will be held offline in Shanghai and will use a double-elimination format. All matches will be BO3.
•The tournament will use the following seven maps: OVERPASS, MIRAGE, INFERNO, DUST2, NUKE, ANCIENT, ANUBIS.
•During Play-In and Group Stage, there will be no coach slot on the server. Coaches may stand behind the players during the match.
2. Schedule
•Play-In Dates: March 26-27, 2026 (Beijing Time)
•Group stage Dates: March 28-29, 2026 (Beijing Time)
•Playoffs Dates: April 1–5, 2026 (Beijing Time)
